# Greenhouse company slugs — EXAMPLE
# Copy this file to config/feed_urls.txt and replace with your target companies.
# Format: one slug per line. The slug is the company identifier in Greenhouse's API.
# The pipeline calls: boards-api.greenhouse.io/v1/boards/{slug}/jobs?content=true
#
# To find a company's slug: look at their jobs page URL, e.g.
#   https://boards.greenhouse.io/acmecorp  →  slug is "acmecorp"
#
# Validate each slug works before adding: curl that URL and check for a jobs list.
#
# Tip: after editing, open /settings/feed-urls/ and click "Verify feed URLs"
# to check that each board still resolves (live / dead / unreachable).
#
# NOTE: Greenhouse is heavily used by tech companies and some modern nonprofits, but
# many employers use other ATSes (Workday, Taleo, iCIMS, Lever, Ashby, SmartRecruiters).
# If your target employers are not on Greenhouse, leave this file empty and rely on
# the LinkedIn/Indeed search queries in jsearch_queries.txt plus the Google Form
# manual ingestion for jobs you find yourself.
#
# See docs/GENERALIZATION.md for notes on adding support for other ATSes.

[replace these lines with slugs for your target companies, or leave empty]
